U.S. stocks fell as declines in
consumer and technology companies wiped out an early rally
triggered by better-than-estimated economic reports.  Apple Inc. lost 1 percent and was the biggest drag on the
Standard & Poorâ€™s 500 Index. Caterpillar Inc., Hewlett-Packard
Co. and International Business Machines Corp. lost at least 0.7
percent for the biggest declines in the Dow Jones Industrial
Average.  The S&P 500 slipped 0.1 percent to 1,143.63 at 11:15 a.m.
